    "summary": "Since the collapse of Rana Plaza in 2013, there is a lot of attention on the (lack of) safety in the Ready-Made Garment industry in Bangladesh. In my view, the most important advance to achieve a sustainable improvement of this safety is made by raising the levels of safety knowledge and awareness throughout the whole supply chain. This is achieved through the training and education of all stakeholders, on all levels: from universities down to the work floor.\n\nI want to use my knowledge and experience by developing training and education programs on safety engineering and management:\n\u2022\tfor the engineers responsible for safe buildings and installations, \n\u2022\tfor the managers responsible for safe operation, and: \n\u2022\tfor the trainers who will train and educate all of those involved in the industry.\n",
